d `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` from environment with default\n121:   - Purpose: Sandbox interpreter identifier\n122:   - Code: `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME = os.environ.get(\"CODEINTERPRETER_NAME\", DEFAULT_INTERPRETER_NAME)`\n123:   - File: `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n124:   - Verification: `grep \"CODEINTERPRETER_NAME\" example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n125: \n126: - [ ] **T3.5**: Load `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` from environment with default\n127:   - Purpose: Kubernetes namespace for sandbox\n128:   - Code: `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE = os.environ.get(\"SANDBOX_NAMESPACE\", DEFAULT_NAMESPACE)`\n129:   - File: `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n130:   - Verification: `grep \"SANDBOX_NAMESPACE\" example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n131: \n132: - [ ] **T3.6**: Load `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` from environment with default\n133:   - Purpose: Sandbox warmup duration\n134:   - Code: `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC = int(os.environ.get(\"SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC\", str(DEFAULT_WARMUP_SEC)))`\n135:   - File: `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n136:   - Verification: `grep \"SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC\" example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n137: \n138: - [ ] **T3.7**: Load `ROUTER_URL` from environment\n139:   - Purpose: AgentCube Router endpoint URL\n140:   - Code: `ROUTER_URL = os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")`\n141:   - File: `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n142:   - Verification: `grep \"ROUTER_URL\" example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n143: \n144: - [ ] **T3.8**: Load `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` from environment\n145:   - Purpose: AgentCube Workload Manager endpoint URL\n146:   - Code: `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL = os.environ.get(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")`\n147:   - File: `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n148:   - Verification: `grep \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\" example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n149: \n150: ### Phase 4: SandboxRunner Class Definition (ST-4)\n151: \n152: - [ ] **T4.1**: Create `pcap_analyzer.py` skeleton with imports\n153:   - Purpose: Module entry point with r